<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">
Note:—This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sledge, W. A." box="[642,803,158,184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref2998" refString="Sledge, W. A. (1981) The Thelypteridaceae of Ceylon. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Botany series 8: 1 - 54." type="book chapter" year="1981">Sledge (1981)</bibRefCitation>
as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hope) Holttum. It" authorityName="Holttum. It" baseAuthorityName="Hope" box="[992,1422,158,185]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Christella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papilio">
<emphasis box="[992,1194,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Christella papilio</emphasis>
(Hope) Holttum. It
</taxonomicName>
is different from 
<taxonomicName box="[299,410,194,221]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Christella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papilio">
<emphasis box="[299,410,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">C. papilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its long creeping rhizome with well-spaced fronds and tetraploid chromosome number (n=72) (
<collectingRegion box="[226,315,230,256]" country="Myanmar" name="Chin" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">Manton</collectingRegion>
and Sledge, 1954). Later, it was renamed 
<taxonomicName box="[779,884,230,256]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Thelypteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sledgei">
<emphasis box="[779,884,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="185">T. sledgei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser-Jenkins, C. R." box="[924,1170,230,256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" refId="ref1979" refString="Fraser-Jenkins, C. R. (1997) New Species Syndrome in Indian Pteridology and the Ferns of Nepal. International Book Distributors, Dehra Dun, India, 403 pp." type="book" year="1997">Fraser-Jenkins (1997)</bibRefCitation>
. This endangered species is confined to streams banks in forests at higher elevations (
<quantity box="[805,958,266,293]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="185" unit="m" value="1850.0" valueMax="2200.0" valueMin="1500.0">1500-2200 m</quantity>
) (Shaffar-Fehre, 2006).
</paragraph>
